==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[παράδειγμα]] (paradeigma) which means "[[pattern]]" or "[[example]]", from the word [[παραδεικνύναι]] (paradeiknunai) meaning "[[demonstrate]]".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈpærədaɪm/}}
*{{audio|en-us-paradigm.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''paradigm''' ([[paradigms]])

# A model or example.
#* ''His prose is a paradigm of clear writing.''
# (''grammar'') The inflections of a word, often displayed as a table.
# A way of [[think]]ing, [[perceive|perceiving]] or [[approach]]ing [[work]] in some [[context]]
# A system of rules and regulations(which may or may not be written down) that do two things: 1)establishes boundaries or limits; 2) tells you how to behave inside the boundaries to achieve success (success is usually measured by your ability to solve problems using the rules)

